title: For Sale/Trade:  Franchi PARA .22 takedown "Assault Rifle"
postcontent: I have for sale or trade a Franchi PARA .22 in excellent condition. It was made in 1979 by Luigi Franchi S.P.A in Breschia Italy. This is a very rare rifle. Stories differ as you research the internet but there were 500 built in total or 5,000 built of which 3,000 were exporte3d or possibly 8,000 built with an unknown quantity exported. In any event, I've personally seen only this one in about 20 years of attending many gun shows. I purchased it fifteen years ago and aside from verifying function at the time, and again today, it has been in the safe the entire time. This rifle breaks into two pieces and fits in the original box which is a wooden box with olive drab canvas cover. It holds 10 rounds and feeds through the butt-stock.Comes with the original sling, original manual (in Italian), safety book, takedown tool, and allen wrench for the setscrew. The rifle is threaded at the muzzle and has the original flash-hider. The gun is beautiful and functions very well. I never have accuracy-tested it but the rifling in the barrel is still very defined. I'm assuming that since it's been a collectible gun from the start that it has seen very few rounds. The gun apparently was built in a small quantity to commemorate Italian Para-troopers. You won't find many like this one. Ironically, this rifle would break many of the rules in the proposed Feinstein legislation. Take-down, pistol grip, military-style butt-stock, adjustable rear distance slide military-style sights, threaded barrel for compensator or silencer, etc. If you need additional photos, I have plenty I can email.

title: For Sale:  AR-15 Palmetto State Armory with Adams Arms Piston system + more  $1649
postcontent:
Up for sale is my Palmetto State Armory AR-15 with many upgrades.  As stock, the AR-15 specs were:

Starts with one of our  chrome-lined Mil-spec steel barrels in the versatile M4 profile, mated to our forged aluminum upper, and finished off with a standard carbine hand guard, Pinned f-marked front sight post and A2 Flash hider.  The forged lower is built with our 6 position Mil-spec size 7075 buffer tube and PSA M4 stock, Standard PSA lower parts kit with A2 Grip and aluminum trigger guard.  The rifle is comes complete with a Magpul rear back up sight.  It comes with one 30 Round D&H Magazine (where allowed by law) so all you have to provide is the ammo to start having fun.

Barrel:  16" chrome-lined mil-spec chrome moly vanadium barrel, chambered in 5.56 NATO, with a 1/7 twist, M4 barrel extension, and a carbine gas system.   M4 style profile is phosphate coated to mil-specs, and is High Pressure tested, and Magnetic Particle inspected, to ensure quality and dependability.   Barrel is made for us by FN Manufacturing here in Columbia, and finished off with a standard carbine hand guard, pinned f-marked front sight post, and A2 flash hider.

Upper: Forged 7075-T6 A3 AR upper is made to MIL-SPECS and hard coat anodized black for durability. Featuring machined T marks, and a mil-spec finish. These uppers are made for us right here in the USA by a mil-spec manufacturer, and are marked with the Palmetto State Armory logo on the left side, up front, just below the rail.

Lower:  These forged lowers are quality made using 7075-T6 aluminum and are marked "MULTI" for caliber.  Finish is Black Hardcoat Anodize per MIL-8625 Type 3 class 2.  7075 aluminum Mil-spec sized buffer tube is dry film lube coated on the inside, has 6 adjustment positions, is paired with a PSA M4 stock and has a staked castle nut.  Standard carbine buffer is Black anodized and has the PSA logo on the face.  Lower is finished with a A2 Grip and aluminum trigger guard.   Equipped with a standard PSA fire control group, the trigger has a smooth pull and clean break.

Since then I purchased the rifle, I've upgraded the AR-15 with an Adams Arms Piston kit.  The original AR-15 design is a direct gas impingement system which blows all the dirty hot gases from combustion back into the chamber and onto the bolt.  This means that your chamber and bolt are filthy by the time you're done shooting and you spend way too much time cleaning the thing.  With the Adams Arms piston kit, the AR-15 is now a piston driven AR-15 and the hot gases get pushed out the front of the rifle away from the chamber and bolt.  If you're ever fired the two side by side, it's like night and day.  You can shoot pretty much all day and your bolt will still be crazy clean and require only a quick wipe down and lube rather than the extensive take apart and cleaning with the classic AR-15 system.

Also upgraded is the grip to a Magpul MOE + grip which has storage compartment on the bottom and also has rubber coating for a more secure grip.  The stock has been upgraded to the Magpul CTR stock which is not only more comfortable, but also locks in place to prevent and movement.  The hand guards are also upgraded to Magpul for a more comfortable grip.  I'm also including an extra Adams Arms gas block and all the original stock parts as show in the photo.  Lastly, I'm including two more Magpul 30 round magazines with windows.

I will NOT ship the rifle anywhere.  If you want to buy it, we'll have to meet face to face.  I will not part the rifle out.  It's either all or none.  If you don't like something on the rifle, feel free to sell that part and replace it with something else.  I'm not interested in any trades at this time.  Lastly, if you're reading this listing, the rifle is still for sale.  

Lowball offers will simply be ignored.  First person who comes with the money, gets the rifle.  Simple as that.  Feel free to contact me to ask any questions, but most of the questions should already be answered above.

Oh, and before I forget, if you're legally not allowed to purchase or own this firearm (a.k.a. convicted felon, etc.), then please don't contact me about purchasing this.
